  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678198551400-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678198551400-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678198551400-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678198551400-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678198551400-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678198555432-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678198555432-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678198555432-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678198555432-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678198555432-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 2 min or until starting to brown, then transfer to a bowl and set aside, reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678198563551-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678198563551-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678198563551-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678198563551-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678198563551-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> with the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>pepper strips</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> with your <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Mix everything together and cook the <strong>chicken</strong> for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678198567693-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678198567693-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678198567693-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678198567693-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678198567693-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once lightly browned, add a couple of splashes of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for a further 10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>smoky pulled chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678198571633-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678198571633-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678198571633-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678198571633-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678198571633-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678198574864-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678198574864-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678198574864-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678198574864-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678198574864-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are done, push them into 1 pile per person on the baking tray[s]</p><p>Top each pile with the <strong>cooked chorizo </strong>and <strong>grated cheese </strong>and return the tray[s] to the oven for 4-5 min or until the cheese has melted</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tortillas</strong> to a plate and pop them in the <strong>microwave </strong>for<strong> </strong>20 secs on high or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678198577914-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678198577914-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678198577914-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678198577914-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1678198577914-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Load up the <strong>warmed tortillas </strong>with the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p>Top with <strong>smoky pulled chicken </strong>and dollop over your <strong>soured cream</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>cheesy chorizo potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
